$ Shell command: chattr
@ chattr



`chattr +i`: Make the file *immutable* so that no one, not even → Linux/user/root, can change, delete or link the file.

`chattr +a`: Make file *append only*. Usable, for example, for log-file security.

`chattr +s`: Secure deletion of the file.

sa:

  → Linux/shell/commands/lsattr[`lsattr`],
  → Linux/filesystem/xattr[`xattr`]

  → Linux/shell/commands/chmod[`chmod`] to change file mode bits.

  → Linux/shell/commands/index[Shell commands]
